
[1]hearken

   HE`ARKEN, v.i. h`arken.

   1. To listen; to lend the ear; to attend to what is uttered, with
   eagerness or curiosity.

   The furies hearken, and their snakes uncurl.

   2. To attend; to regard; to give heed to what is uttered; to observe or
   obey.

   Hearken, O Israel, to the statutes and the judgments which I teach you.
   Deut.4.

   3. To listen;; to attend; to grant or comply with.

   Hearken thou to the supplication of thy servant.

   l Kings 8.

        HE`ARKEN, v.t. h`arken. To hear by listening. [Little used.]
